Who's News:
   McDonnell Douglas
   Picks New Presidents
   At Two Subsidiaries
The defense contractor and commercial aerospace concern
also named Dean C. Borgman president of McDonnell Douglas
Helicopter Co., Mesa, Ariz., effective March 23. Mr. Borgman,
50, had been acting president for a month, having succeeded
Thomas M. Gunn. Mr. Gunn, 48, had been named corporate vice
president for special projects.
   Patrick R. McGinnis, 56, was appointed to the newly
created post of executive vice president of McDonnell Douglas
Helicopter. Before retiring from McDonnell Douglas last
April, he had been chief financial officer and vice
president-general manager for the company's Douglas Aircraft
Co. unit in Long Beach, Calif.